    Support resources for students              UIC COVID-19 Emergency Grant Awards to Students (April 27, 2020)  UIC is pleased to announce a $15.9 million emergency grant program.  The Department of Education has allocated $14.9 million for this grant through the CARES Act. In addition to the Department of Education funding, UIC has transferred $1 million from the Federal Work-Study Program as allowed by the federal government to supplement the emergency grant funding for any student eligible for Title IV Financial Aid funding.  Undergraduate, graduate and professional students enrolled in the Spring Semester can be eligible to receive up to $1,000, and Pell eligible undergraduate students can qualify for an additional $1,000.   Full details        UIC Guidance on  COVID-19 Policies       School of Public Health Communications        Speech bubble icon        Message to SPH Community        Check icon        Building Access Form        Flag icon         Cleaning Info        Matrix icon                Remote Work Info              Volunteer Opportunities  School of Public Health students and alumni are needed for volunteer opportunities with public health agencies, community groups and with UIC-led initiatives.   Learn more        Free Campus Parking  with I-Card      COVID-19 UIC  Information Site       University messages on Coronavirus   Each of the messages below is linked to the official message on the UIC Coronavirus hub page.  Please note:  while the university lists the date for conversion to all online classes as March 23, all School of Public Health courses will be fully online by March 18.      List of messages        Returning library materials  May 7, 2020          Virtual graduation celebration May 16  May 4, 2020          Planning for fall semester at UIC  May 1, 2020          Supporting Asians and Asian Americans at UIC  April 27, 2020          UIC COVID-19 Emergency Grant Awards to Students  April 27, 2020          Important Info About Summer 2020 